---
import Base from '@layouts/Base.astro';
import Button from '@components/Button.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="Varax Labs builds open-source Kubernetes tools. Our mission is to make Kubernetes compliance accessible to every team.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">

    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold text-light-text dark:text-dark-text mb-6">
      About Varax Labs
    </h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-base text-light-text-secondary dark:text-dark-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Varax Labs builds Kubernetes-native tools for operations teams. We believe that
        monitoring and compliance shouldn't require expensive SaaS platforms, vendor lock-in,
        or sending your cluster data to third parties.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-light-text dark:text-dark-text pt-4">Our Mission</h2>
      <p>
        Make Kubernetes compliance accessible to every team — from two-person startups to
        enterprise platform teams. Compliance tooling should be as easy to install as any
        other operator in your cluster.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-light-text dark:text-dark-text pt-4">Why We Built This</h2>
      <p>
        We spent years running production Kubernetes clusters and dealing with the same pain
        points every team faces: CronJobs failing silently, compliance audits requiring weeks
        of manual evidence gathering, and security benchmarks that nobody had time to check.
      </p>
      <p>
        So we built the tools we wished existed. <strong class="text-light-text dark:text-dark-text">Varax Monitor</strong> solves
        CronJob observability with one Helm command. <strong class="text-light-text dark:text-dark-text">Varax</strong> automates SOC2
        compliance scanning and report generation — entirely within your cluster.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-light-text dark:text-dark-text pt-4">Open Source Commitment</h2>
      <p>
        Varax Monitor is free forever under the Apache 2.0 license. The Varax compliance
        platform's core scanning engine is also open source. We believe in building trust
        through transparency — you can read every line of code that runs in your cluster.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our business model is simple: the free tools build community and trust. The commercial
        compliance platform (Pro tier) generates revenue through audit-ready reporting features
        that save teams weeks of manual work.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <Button href="https://github.com/varaxlabs" variant="secondary" external>View our GitHub</Button>
      <Button href="/monitor" variant="ghost">Explore Varax Monitor</Button>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
